This paper deals with natural language understanding and coreference resolution, which are typically studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural models, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of syntactic structure, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also possible sub-categories, as they often overlap with NLP and computational linguistics.
